Spec: Product Plugin Sources

Purpose:
  Own product-specific plugin package templates generated into plugin submodules.

Structure:
  ./codex/**: Codex plugin manifest and README source.
  ./claude/**: Claude Code plugin manifest and README source.
  ./copilot/**: GitHub Copilot skills package README source.
  ./junie/**: Junie skills package README source.
  ./cline/**: Cline skills package README source.
  ./antigravity/**: Antigravity plugin manifest and README source.

Owns:
  ./codex/**
  ./claude/**
  ./copilot/**
  ./junie/**
  ./cline/**
  ./antigravity/**

Must:
  Keep product-specific manifests, README files, and product-only metadata here.
  Make product README files explain that plugin repositories are generated from `https://github.com/specdd/agent-plugins`.
  Make product README files include install commands for the target product.
  Use the `specdd/specdd` marketplace install path only when the target product supports it.
  Document GitHub Copilot installation with explicit `gh skill install` commands for each skill.
  Document Junie and Cline manual copy installation as the primary path, with `gh skill install` as a secondary tracked path.
  Keep Antigravity as a native plugin package with root `plugin.json` and generated `skills/*/SKILL.md`.
  Share common skills, fragments, assets, and licenses through parent source areas instead of duplicating them here.
  Keep paths inside manifests relative to the generated plugin root.

Must not:
  Store generated `skills` output here.
  Duplicate shared assets or repository license text.
